text: The German Turnfest 1933 took place in Stuttgart. It was carried out from 21 to 31 July. The patron was President Paul von Hindenburg. The Turnfest attracted 600,000 people, 120,000 taking part in the games. == External links == * Deutsches Turnfest 1933 on the Website of the Deutschen Turnerbundes Category:1933 in German sport Category:History of Stuttgart
title: Deutsches Turnfest 1933
